WEBVTT

00:12.066 --> 00:16.333
[bright tones]

00:16.400 --> 00:19.333
[tense jazzy music]

00:19.400 --> 00:26.433
♪ ♪

01:46.433 --> 01:48.600
- I don't wanna fight nobody!

01:48.667 --> 01:52.934
- In America we all have
certain inalienable rights.

01:53.000 --> 01:54.400
Like the right
to bear arms,

01:54.467 --> 01:57.266
and the right
to remain silent.

01:57.333 --> 02:00.367
But the state has
the ultimate right.

02:00.433 --> 02:03.166
It can kill us.

02:03.233 --> 02:06.333
And due to popular demand,
Governor James Devlin,

02:06.400 --> 02:07.900
revived capital punishment,

02:09.834 --> 02:11.867
and he decided that
Jefferson Keane,

02:11.934 --> 02:13.066
a man he doesn't know,

02:13.133 --> 02:15.633
a man he will
never even meet,

02:15.700 --> 02:17.367
should be put to death.

02:17.433 --> 02:20.567
Should be put down
like a rabid dog.

02:20.633 --> 02:21.834
- No!

02:21.900 --> 02:24.100
- The mood in this
country has changed.

02:24.166 --> 02:26.500
People are sick of crime,
sick of being afraid.

02:26.567 --> 02:28.333
They need a sign that
something's being done.

02:28.400 --> 02:29.967
- Even, Governor,
if it's been proven

02:30.033 --> 02:31.467
that executions have no effect

02:31.533 --> 02:33.300
on the increase or decrease
of crime whatsoever?

02:33.367 --> 02:35.166
- Especially
if it has no effect.

02:35.233 --> 02:37.967
These days,
murders are random, senseless.

02:38.033 --> 02:40.300
Maybe the punishment
should be, too.

02:40.367 --> 02:42.900
Jefferson Keane will
be the first person executed

02:42.967 --> 02:45.567
by this state in 34 years.
He's the first,

02:45.633 --> 02:47.700
because he snapped the neck
of another inmate.

02:47.767 --> 02:49.333
He's the first
because he deserves to die.

02:49.400 --> 02:52.400
- Jefferson Keane is the first
because he's black and young.

02:52.467 --> 02:53.600
The public is not
gonna feel safe

02:53.667 --> 02:55.533
if we execute
a 70-year-old white guy.

02:55.600 --> 02:56.867
- You're not gonna turn this
into a racial thing

02:56.934 --> 02:58.266
with me are you?
- Oh, please.

02:58.333 --> 02:59.800
- Has anybody thought about
all the protesters

02:59.867 --> 03:01.333
we're gonna have outside?

03:01.400 --> 03:03.200
Marching around,
yelling slogans,

03:03.266 --> 03:05.333
and then the counter-protesters
yelling at them?

03:05.400 --> 03:08.367
- Yeah, and we'll have
even less parking spaces.

03:12.633 --> 03:14.633
- The protesters aren't
gonna be a problem.

03:14.700 --> 03:17.767
- I want you to know that
when those protesters come,

03:17.834 --> 03:19.166
I'm standing with them.

03:19.233 --> 03:20.867
- I can't have an
employee of mine

03:20.934 --> 03:22.533
out there at a vigil

03:22.600 --> 03:24.367
holding a candle
in front of a camera.

03:24.433 --> 03:26.367
- The last time I looked,
we had freedom of speech

03:26.433 --> 03:28.400
and freedom of assembly
in this country,

03:28.467 --> 03:30.066
or did you guys eliminate
those rights too?

03:30.133 --> 03:31.900
- The governor's
been biting my ass,

03:31.967 --> 03:33.700
saying he's gonna
make more budget cuts,

03:33.767 --> 03:34.967
and he means it.

03:35.033 --> 03:38.266
Up to and including your job.

03:38.333 --> 03:40.066
- Is this a threat?

03:40.133 --> 03:42.066
I've got a job, Leo.

03:42.133 --> 03:44.266
I've got a permanent vocation.

03:44.333 --> 03:46.700
I can go teach fifth-grade kids
at Cathedral School.

03:46.767 --> 03:49.100
I can go be a missionary
in Pago Pago.

03:49.166 --> 03:50.667
- [sighs]

03:50.734 --> 03:52.300
Don't join the protesters.

03:52.367 --> 03:54.233
- And if I do?

03:54.300 --> 03:57.533
- You're fired.

04:03.800 --> 04:07.367
- Well, that's fine.

04:07.433 --> 04:10.367
[soft dramatic music]

04:10.433 --> 04:14.834
♪ ♪

04:14.900 --> 04:17.834
I'll send you a postcard
from Pago Pago.

04:18.934 --> 04:20.300
- Hey, Markstram, man,

04:20.367 --> 04:22.500
what if Keane
didn't kill Martinez, huh?

04:22.567 --> 04:24.200
Look, what if they got
the wrong man?

04:24.266 --> 04:26.100
- He did it, Kenny.
- Look, man, I know he did it.

04:26.166 --> 04:28.000
I'm saying
what if he didn't do it?

04:28.066 --> 04:30.333
- I don't understand.
- All I'm saying, Dino, is

04:30.400 --> 04:32.233
makes you wonder
what the guy's doin'

04:32.300 --> 04:33.633
what the guy's thinking,

04:33.700 --> 04:35.467
sitting on death row,
knowing he's gonna die.

04:35.533 --> 04:37.533
- The only difference
between you and him, Joey,

04:37.600 --> 04:40.166
is he knows the
exact date he'll die.

04:40.233 --> 04:41.834
- So the state's
gonna let Keane choose

04:41.900 --> 04:43.667
