08:10.200 --> 08:12.233
I'm glad.
- But...

08:12.300 --> 08:14.433
- "But--but" what?

08:17.400 --> 08:20.367
- Nothing, sir.
- [grunts]

08:20.433 --> 08:22.767
Don't forget,
a little starch.

08:22.834 --> 08:24.033
- So I'll go to McManus,

08:24.100 --> 08:25.734
tell him what might
have happened in the gym,

08:25.800 --> 08:28.467
get him to investigate.
- You can't.

08:28.533 --> 08:29.767
- Why not?

08:29.834 --> 08:31.367
- If you say anything,
they'll kill you.

08:31.433 --> 08:33.100
- They who?

08:33.166 --> 08:34.533
- Exactly.

08:34.600 --> 08:35.800
- Hey, Beecher.

08:35.867 --> 08:37.600
Sorry I got
a little testy before.

08:37.667 --> 08:39.667
- That's okay.

08:39.734 --> 08:41.200
- You wanna get high?

08:41.266 --> 08:43.900
- No, thanks, man,
not right now.

08:43.967 --> 08:46.033
Kind of trying
to keep my head clean.

08:46.100 --> 08:48.300
- Later.

08:50.967 --> 08:53.033
- What I should do,
is represent Keane

08:53.100 --> 08:55.000
and appeal his
murder conviction.

08:55.066 --> 08:57.367
- You?
- I'm a lawyer.

08:57.433 --> 08:59.400
- The state disbarred you.

08:59.467 --> 09:02.433
- The state can't take away
what I do, who I am.

09:02.500 --> 09:05.066
I can help the man.

09:05.133 --> 09:07.200
He killed Martinez
in self-defense.

09:07.266 --> 09:08.467
He shouldn't die.

09:08.533 --> 09:09.967
- You need to
talk to Keane himself,

09:10.033 --> 09:11.934
find out what really
went on that day.

09:12.000 --> 09:15.600
- Yeah, I know, but getting
into death row isn't easy.

09:15.667 --> 09:17.900
- I have a way.

09:20.333 --> 09:24.166
- I'm in fear for my life.
- From who?

09:24.233 --> 09:26.800
- I can't say.
You know I can't say.

09:26.867 --> 09:29.133
I need you to put me
in protective custody.

09:29.200 --> 09:30.433
- You can't be
going in and out

09:30.500 --> 09:32.200
of protective custody
whenever you want.

09:32.266 --> 09:33.867
It's to be used
only in extreme cases.

09:33.934 --> 09:35.533
- Well, this is.

09:35.600 --> 09:36.767
- Next time
you ask for protection,

09:36.834 --> 09:39.433
I may say no.
- I'll take that risk.

09:56.166 --> 09:57.800
Keane?

10:00.166 --> 10:01.767
Keane?

10:03.867 --> 10:06.300
Keane!

10:06.367 --> 10:07.900
- Who wants me?

10:07.967 --> 10:10.633
- Beecher.
Tobias Beecher.

10:10.700 --> 10:12.400
I need to talk to you
about your trial.

10:12.467 --> 10:13.834
I read your transcript.

10:13.900 --> 10:15.266
You weren't very cooperative
with your attorneys.

10:15.333 --> 10:16.734
I killed Martinez.

10:16.800 --> 10:19.633
- Why didn't you tell
the lawyers you were set up?

10:19.700 --> 10:21.400
- Look.

10:21.467 --> 10:24.767
Johnny Post killed Dino Ortolani
because I told him to.

10:24.834 --> 10:27.967
Now the Wiseguys know that.
Now they want me dead.

10:28.033 --> 10:29.367
If they kill me,

10:29.433 --> 10:31.300
one of my homeboys
is gonna kill them,

10:31.367 --> 10:33.233
and then they're gonna kill
another one of my boys,

10:33.300 --> 10:36.166
and on and on and on.

10:36.233 --> 10:37.934
My death can put an end to that.

10:38.000 --> 10:40.066
- Not necessarily.

10:40.133 --> 10:42.533
- Look, if I die,

10:42.600 --> 10:44.633
I feel like
I might go to heaven now,

10:44.700 --> 10:46.400
but if I go back to Em City,

10:46.467 --> 10:48.500
I might go back to my old ways.

10:48.567 --> 10:51.200
I may lose my faith,
my soul.

10:52.600 --> 10:55.300
I'm at peace right now, Beecher.

10:55.367 --> 10:57.033
