- As the day of execution
draws near, tension grows.

15:28.867 --> 15:30.467
Both outside the walls at

15:30.533 --> 15:33.667
the Oswald Maximum Security
Penitentiary, and inside,

15:33.734 --> 15:36.667
where the debate on the
death penalty is no less fierce.

15:36.734 --> 15:38.100
- I don't believe in murder.

15:38.166 --> 15:40.667
First degree, abortion,
or by jury decree.

15:40.734 --> 15:43.233
It's all murder!
- Lethal injection?

15:43.300 --> 15:45.166
What's wrong with the
good old electric chair?

15:45.233 --> 15:47.700
- Jefferson Keane will die
tomorrow in this prison.

15:47.767 --> 15:49.166
In light of the historic,
moral,

15:49.233 --> 15:50.767
and political nature
of the event,

15:50.834 --> 15:53.400
we might lose sight
of the human factors involved.

15:53.467 --> 15:55.133
We spoke today
with Cornelius Keane,

15:55.200 --> 15:57.400
the inmate's father,
and Helen Martinez,

15:57.467 --> 15:58.767
mother of the murder victim.

15:58.834 --> 16:00.467
- You teach a boy
right from wrong,

16:00.533 --> 16:03.467
then you just hope--
you just hope for the best.

16:03.533 --> 16:06.767
- I want him dead!

16:06.834 --> 16:10.633
I want him
in the ground, dead!

16:10.700 --> 16:12.734
Dead!
Dead!

16:12.800 --> 16:13.734
- [exhales]

16:13.800 --> 16:15.900
[slaps door]
- Hey.

16:15.967 --> 16:17.800
- Jefferson Keane's sister's
in kidney failure.

16:17.867 --> 16:19.500
They think she'll die.

16:19.567 --> 16:22.467
- Oh, this is just great.

16:22.533 --> 16:26.100
Well, life just keeps
getting better and better.

16:26.166 --> 16:29.700
I fucked this up
from the get-ready.

16:29.767 --> 16:31.200
Ortolani's dead 'cause of me

16:31.266 --> 16:35.133
and now Keane's gonna join him.

16:35.200 --> 16:36.533
- You think you're responsible

16:36.600 --> 16:39.800
for that bad boy
being on death row?

16:42.767 --> 16:44.100
Timmy...

16:44.166 --> 16:47.033
and I mean this
in the nicest way possible...

16:47.100 --> 16:49.333
you are one fucked-up guy.

16:49.400 --> 16:51.467
- Hmm...

16:51.533 --> 16:54.600
Well...

16:54.667 --> 16:56.500
Does that mean we're not
going to the play tonight?

16:56.567 --> 16:58.700
- [laughs softly]
- Doctor...

16:58.767 --> 17:00.033
We need you.

17:00.100 --> 17:03.033
[jazzy dramatic music]

17:03.100 --> 17:06.033
- [mumbling]

17:06.100 --> 17:07.667
♪ ♪

17:07.734 --> 17:09.767
- On three.
One, two, three.

17:09.834 --> 17:11.700
♪ ♪

17:11.767 --> 17:14.300
We should run some tests.

17:14.367 --> 17:16.000
- I'm gonna be fine.

17:16.066 --> 17:19.033
- Hey, some say there are
five stages of death:

17:19.100 --> 17:22.433
denial, anger, bargaining,

17:22.500 --> 17:23.800
depression,

17:23.867 --> 17:26.800
and finally, acceptance.

17:27.600 --> 17:29.400
The moment when you say
to yourself,

17:29.467 --> 17:30.600
"I'm gonna die,

17:30.667 --> 17:32.000
and ain't shit
I can do about it."

17:32.066 --> 17:33.600
[chuckles]

17:33.667 --> 17:37.033
Oh yeah, in Oz,
we know all about that.

17:37.100 --> 17:39.500
We know all about acceptance.

17:39.567 --> 17:41.800
- Look at your hair.

17:41.867 --> 17:44.166
Come on,
let me braid it for you.

17:44.233 --> 17:46.600
- Nah, that's all right.

17:46.667 --> 17:48.000
- C'mon, I'll make your hair
look so nice,

17:48.066 --> 17:49.300
they won't wanna kill you.

17:49.367 --> 17:51.934
[both laugh]

17:52.000 --> 17:52.934
Come on.
- You crazy.

17:53.000 --> 17:55.700
Come on.

17:55.767 --> 17:58.633
- If you really want to.

18:03.133 --> 18:06.834
- I saw pop on TV yesterday.
- Yeah?

18:06.900 --> 18:09.300
- Talking about you,

18:09.367 --> 18:12.433
talking about our family.

18:13.767 --> 18:17.066
Sorry I ain't who
you want me to be.

18:17.133 --> 18:20.500
I like being queer.
[sniffles]

18:25.734 --> 18:27.000
[crying softly]

18:27.066 --> 18:28.967
- I love you, Billie.

18:29.033 --> 18:31.166
Allah loves you.

18:31.233 --> 18:33.800
- But dad don't.

18:35.600 --> 18:37.166
- Jefferson--

18:37.233 --> 18:39.900
I'm sorry, Tizi...

18:39.967 --> 18:41.934
I've got some bad news.

18:42.000 --> 18:45.500
Your sister Grace
is in the hospital.

18:45.567 --> 18:47.567
Kidney failure.

18:47.633 --> 18:50.266
The doctors think that
she'll probably die soon

18:50.333 --> 18:53.700
unless she gets a transplant,
but organs are scarce.

18:53.767 --> 18:55.467
- Why don't you
take one of mine?

18:55.533 --> 18:58.667
Not like I'm gonna
use it much longer.

18:58.734 --> 19:00.266
Make that happen, McManus.

19:00.333 --> 19:02.266
- I'll try.
- No, you do more than try.

19:02.333 --> 19:03.934
Make it happen.

19:05.367 --> 19:07.333
Make it happen!

19:07.400 --> 19:10.433
(crowd yelling)

19:21.633 --> 19:22.934
- [sighs]

19:23.000 --> 19:24.900
The governor says no,
he won't grant a stay.

19:24.967 --> 19:26.767
- Fuck.

19:26.834 --> 19:29.533
Even that little prick Devlin
can't be that heartless.

19:29.600 --> 19:31.100
- He says Keane
is too dangerous

19:31.166 --> 19:32.300
to be released
to a hospital.

19:32.367 --> 19:34.900
- He's changed.

19:34.967 --> 19:38.800
- This conversion of his
could be bullshit.

19:38.867 --> 19:42.000
- I talked to him, Leo.
It's real.

19:42.066 --> 19:43.467
We gotta fight
for this one.

19:43.533 --> 19:45.166
- How?

19:45.233 --> 19:47.166
If we go public,
we stoke the protesters.

19:47.233 --> 19:48.667
Piss Devlin off even more.

19:48.734 --> 19:50.300
- Devlin thinks he's God.

19:50.367 --> 19:51.934
- Yeah.

19:52.000 --> 19:54.266
- Maybe it's time we got
some help from the real one.

19:54.333 --> 19:57.734
- You want me to call
the cardinal to intercede?

19:57.800 --> 19:59.500
- Yes.
- Tim.

19:59.567 --> 20:01.300
Cardinal Abgott is
more conservative than

20:01.367 --> 20:05.567
Jesse Helms and Bill Buckly
all rolled into one.

20:05.633 --> 20:07.800
He once gave a speech
where he justified

20:07.867 --> 20:10.100
the torture
of the Holy Inquisition.

20:10.166 --> 20:11.600
- That's fucked up,
even so,

20:11.667 --> 20:13.567
you gotta make the call.
- [scoffs]

20:13.633 --> 20:14.900
You make the call.

20:14.967 --> 20:16.900
- What, Ray,
are you afraid?

20:16.967 --> 20:18.467
- No, of course
I'm not afraid.

20:18.533 --> 20:20.100
- Then?

20:23.133 --> 20:26.166
- Why do you think
that I work here, huh, Tim?

20:26.233 --> 20:29.033
I went to the
Pontifical Gregorian University

20:29.100 --> 20:31.367
in the Vatican.
I was in the top of my class.

20:31.433 --> 20:34.834
I was the cardinal's
"Great Yellow Hope",

20:34.900 --> 20:36.400
until I started working
in his office

20:36.467 --> 20:38.300
and I just asked
a few too many questions.

20:38.367 --> 20:41.333
I had a few
too many opinions.

20:41.400 --> 20:44.000
I defied him...

20:44.066 --> 20:47.300
Instead of
deifying him.

20:47.367 --> 20:49.467
So His Excellency decided
to punish me

20:49.533 --> 20:52.233
by sending me to Oz

20:52.300 --> 20:54.200
to extinguish
my career.

20:54.266 --> 20:56.100
- So Jefferson Keane's
sister dies

20:56.166 --> 20:59.100
because you and the cardinal
had a tiff?

20:59.166 --> 21:00.767
- I didn't say
I wouldn't make the call.

21:00.834 --> 21:02.200
I'll make the call.

21:02.266 --> 21:03.667
I'm just warning you,
it probably won't...

21:03.734 --> 21:05.200
[door closes]

21:06.834 --> 21:08.200
Do any good.

21:11.834 --> 21:14.033
- Sorry to disturb you.

21:17.000 --> 21:19.166
- You've come about
the transplant.

21:19.233 --> 21:20.500
- Governor James Devlin,

21:20.567 --> 21:22.200
under pressure
from religious leaders,

21:22.266 --> 21:25.200
including Sheik Zahir Farrah
and Francis Cardinal Abgott,

21:25.266 --> 21:27.333
has granted a 30-day
stay of execution

21:27.400 --> 21:28.867
to Jefferson Keane...
(cheers)

21:28.934 --> 21:30.800
The man convicted
of killing another inmate

21:30.867 --> 21:32.834
at Oswald Maximum
Security Penitentiary.

21:32.900 --> 21:35.800
Keane will donate a kidney
to an ailing sister.

21:35.867 --> 21:38.300
He is expected to go into
surgery sometime today.

21:38.367 --> 21:40.233
The governor was
quick to point out that

21:40.300 --> 21:41.633
all medical costs
are being covered

21:41.700 --> 21:43.433
by the family's own insurance.

21:43.500 --> 21:46.700
- "Clemency" that's
a fancy word for "mercy."

21:46.767 --> 21:49.500
You see, the governor
can commute a death sentence.

21:49.567 --> 21:53.000
He has the power to just
pick up the phone and say no.

21:53.066 --> 21:54.333
But to me,

21:54.400 --> 21:57.266
the only time
the governor shows clemency

21:57.333 --> 21:59.834
is when he don't
make that call,

21:59.900 --> 22:02.700
'cause life in prison
without parole

22:02.767 --> 22:05.834
is a shitload
worse than death.

22:05.900 --> 22:07.767
Death is parole.

22:07.834 --> 22:10.734
Death is the real mercy.

22:10.800 --> 22:12.100
- King me.
- Oh, fuck.

22:12.166 --> 22:13.567
- [laughs]
- O'Reily...

22:13.633 --> 22:14.734
- Yeah.
- Come here.

22:14.800 --> 22:15.900
- Why?
- Because I say.

22:15.967 --> 22:17.667
- So?
- We got business.

22:17.734 --> 22:19.367
- Don't move any pieces,
I got 'em memorized.

22:19.433 --> 22:20.734
- [laughs]
Would I do that?

22:20.800 --> 22:22.333
- Uh, yeah.
- Man, what do you think of me?

22:22.400 --> 22:23.834
- Hey, Joey.
I'm here.

22:23.900 --> 22:25.166
You bet Detroit
on the Sox/Tigers game?

22:25.233 --> 22:26.266
- Yeah.
- You lost.

22:26.333 --> 22:27.433
- Fucking Thomas.
- You owe.

22:27.500 --> 22:28.567
- I know.
- So?

22:28.633 --> 22:29.900
- I'm good for it.
- Says you.

22:29.967 --> 22:31.300
- What, I haven't paid before?
- I want it now.

22:31.367 --> 22:32.533
- Why?
- 'Cause you owe.

22:32.600 --> 22:33.767
- Why you busting my balls?

22:33.834 --> 22:35.033
- 'Cause I don't
like your face.

22:35.100 --> 22:36.633
- Hey, pal, take a look
in the mirror.

22:36.700 --> 22:38.033
- You wanna die?
- You wanna try it?

22:38.100 --> 22:40.000
Problem, guys?
- Yeah, the joint smells

22:40.066 --> 22:41.266
of too much...
[sniffs]

22:41.333 --> 22:42.934
Garlic.
Come on.

22:43.000 --> 22:45.834
- D'Angelo, count to ten
and walk away.

22:45.900 --> 22:48.800
Fucking dago jizzbag.

22:52.533 --> 22:53.800
- You lose, white boy.

22:53.867 --> 22:56.633
- No, I never lose
when it counts.

22:58.367 --> 23:00.900
I'm telling you,
Jefferson was set up.

23:00.967 --> 23:02.567
- By who?
- Come on.

23:02.633 --> 23:03.834
You don't have
to be John Thompson

23:03.900 --> 23:05.367
to figure out
the game plan.

23:05.433 --> 23:07.834
- I know it was
the Wiseguys that did it.

23:07.900 --> 23:09.867
- Schibetta sent Jefferson
to the gladiator ring?

23:09.934 --> 23:11.867
- No, not Schibetta.

23:11.934 --> 23:13.533
I've been asking around.

23:13.600 --> 23:16.166
Looks like Joey D'Angelo
was roguing.

23:16.233 --> 23:17.533
Ever since Ortolani croaked

23:17.600 --> 23:18.934
D'Angelo's been
wanting to move up,

23:19.000 --> 23:21.033
but the old man's been slow,

23:21.100 --> 23:22.600
so D'Angelo
took it on himself

23:22.667 --> 23:24.700
to off Jefferson
just to impress the old man.

23:24.767 --> 23:26.800
- That fuckin' mook,
D'Angelo?

23:26.867 --> 23:28.967
If D'Angelo got Jefferson
the death penalty,

23:29.033 --> 23:30.200
we gotta execute that mother--
- Shut up.

23:30.767 --> 23:32.667
- I swear to g--

23:37.233 --> 23:40.700
- Look, you fellows
do what you gotta do,

23:40.767 --> 23:43.767
but with all the shit that's
been goin' on around here,

23:43.834 --> 23:45.934
if you whack D'Angelo,

23:46.000 --> 23:47.633
Glynn's gonna lock us down
for good.

23:47.700 --> 23:49.333
- So what are we
supposed to do?

23:49.400 --> 23:51.567
- You two work
in the kitchen, right?

23:51.633 --> 23:54.300
- D'Angelo works
in the kitchen.

23:54.367 --> 23:56.166
Maybe he has
a little accident.

23:56.233 --> 23:57.834
- Yeah, yeah, I like that.
- Yeah, yeah.

23:59.033 --> 24:02.467
And why you so hot on justice
for Jefferson now, white boy?

24:02.533 --> 24:03.934
Hmm?

24:04.000 --> 24:05.900
- 'Cause Jefferson took care
of Ortolani for me.

24:05.967 --> 24:07.300
I owe him.

24:07.367 --> 24:09.100
- Good morning.

24:09.166 --> 24:11.600
I'm Carlton Auerbach...
- Who?

24:11.667 --> 24:14.667
- And, as you know,
Sister Peter--

24:14.734 --> 24:17.567
Sister Peter Marie
is not around,

24:17.633 --> 24:19.900
so the--the warden asked me
to pinch hit.

24:19.967 --> 24:22.900
- We want Sister Pete.
- [clears throat]

24:22.967 --> 24:25.633
She's not here.
So, uh, today we're gonna be--

24:25.700 --> 24:28.000
- Shut the fuck up!

24:28.066 --> 24:29.734
[laughter]
- Thank you.

24:29.800 --> 24:33.900
Today we're gonna talk
about anger management.

24:33.967 --> 24:36.533
Controlling the savage beast
inside you.

24:36.600 --> 24:39.633
[all grunting]

24:41.000 --> 24:43.133
- You fuck!

24:45.266 --> 24:46.300
- Fuck!

24:46.367 --> 24:49.400
[screams]

24:50.700 --> 24:54.133
[knocks]
- Mr. Schibetta...

24:54.200 --> 24:56.567
Can I come in?

24:59.166 --> 25:01.033
I heard what happened
to Joey.

25:01.100 --> 25:03.200
Steam pipe bursts,
knocks him backward,

25:03.266 --> 25:04.633
hits him in the head.

25:04.700 --> 25:06.734
Is he okay?
- He's unconscious.

25:06.800 --> 25:08.333
He'll be laid up
for a while.

25:08.400 --> 25:10.033
- I don't mean
to be reaching,

25:10.100 --> 25:12.734
but if you ever need
an extra hand,

25:12.800 --> 25:14.100
I mean, come one.

25:14.166 --> 25:16.333
I-I-I took care of
Jefferson Keane for you.

25:16.400 --> 25:19.133
He's going to die and both
our hands are clean.

25:21.200 --> 25:23.066
- One of my best buddies
in the army

25:23.133 --> 25:26.367
was Donny O'Reily,

25:26.433 --> 25:28.600
Irish guy...

25:28.667 --> 25:30.200
From Howard Beach.

25:30.266 --> 25:32.900
Tough little fucker didn't
take any bullshit from anybody,

25:32.967 --> 25:35.066
including the sergeant.

25:36.033 --> 25:38.066
He loved women,

25:38.133 --> 25:39.333
he loved boats.

25:39.400 --> 25:42.000
He loved
women on boats.

25:42.066 --> 25:44.200
He loved vodka.

25:44.266 --> 25:47.367
He loved women
who drank vodka on boats.

25:51.800 --> 25:53.800
Who knows?

25:53.867 --> 25:56.100
Maybe we can
do some business.

25:56.166 --> 25:57.767
- Okay.

26:02.633 --> 26:05.633
[soft dramatic music]

26:05.700 --> 26:12.667
♪ ♪

26:12.734 --> 26:15.266
[machines beeping]

26:15.333 --> 26:17.166
- Poor son-of-a-bitch.

26:21.166 --> 26:23.166
- [laughs]
Yo, padre.

26:23.233 --> 26:26.700
- How you doing?
- How's my baby.

26:26.767 --> 26:29.467
- He's not doing
so good, Miguel.

26:29.533 --> 26:32.000
He's not getting
any better.

26:32.066 --> 26:33.567
- Shit!

26:33.633 --> 26:35.467
- The doctors...

26:35.533 --> 26:37.867
they're thinking of taking him
off the life support.

26:37.934 --> 26:39.934
- What do you mean,
pull the plug?

26:40.000 --> 26:42.400
No, no, no, no.

26:42.467 --> 26:44.166
- Maritza thinks it's
the best thing, too.

26:44.233 --> 26:45.767
- No, Maritza's sweet.
She gonna listen

26:45.834 --> 26:48.066
to anything
anybody tells her to.

26:48.133 --> 26:49.800
I don't want them
to kill my baby.

26:49.867 --> 26:52.467
- They're not killing
the baby, Miguel.

26:52.533 --> 26:54.433
The machine's are the only
thing keeping the baby alive.

26:54.500 --> 26:56.166
If they turn the machines off,
then the baby can have

26:56.233 --> 26:58.266
a natural death.
- I want to speak to Maritza.

26:58.333 --> 26:59.700
I want to see my baby
right now.

26:59.767 --> 27:02.000
- You can't see Maritza.
You can't see the baby.

27:02.066 --> 27:04.767
They're not even gonna
let you make a phone call.

27:04.834 --> 27:06.834
They're gonna start a
psychiatric evaluation of you.

27:06.900 --> 27:08.266
- They think I'm a bug?

27:08.333 --> 27:09.834
- You cut yourself all up!

27:09.900 --> 27:10.900
- So?

27:10.967 --> 27:12.400
I did it for the baby.

27:12.467 --> 27:14.734
- What do you mean you
"did it for the baby"?

27:14.800 --> 27:16.567
- You tellin' me I gave
the baby life, right?

27:16.633 --> 27:18.300
That he's my responsibility.

27:18.367 --> 27:19.433
Well, the baby being sick,

27:19.500 --> 27:20.967
you know,
I don't know what to do.

27:21.033 --> 27:22.567
I ain't a fucking doctor.

27:22.633 --> 27:25.133
- And slashing your face
did what, huh?

27:25.200 --> 27:27.567
- That's between me and god.

27:27.633 --> 27:29.266
- Oh, Miguel, you tell
the shrink that

27:29.333 --> 27:31.633
and you're gonna be in here
till you're 90-years-old.

27:31.700 --> 27:33.800
- You gotta help me.

27:33.867 --> 27:35.934
You gotta get me
out of here.

27:36.000 --> 27:38.233
You gotta help me
see my baby.

27:38.300 --> 27:41.233
You gotta tell them
not to kill it.

27:41.300 --> 27:43.900
You gotta--
you gotta let me see my baby!

27:43.967 --> 27:46.166
You gotta tell them
not to kill it!

27:46.233 --> 27:47.834
I wanna see my baby!

27:47.900 --> 27:51.233
- You see, I got Alvarez
on the road to redemption.

27:51.300 --> 27:53.700
I got him to start caring,

27:53.767 --> 27:56.166
and I guess that's
tearing him up inside.

27:56.233 --> 27:58.967
- The doctor at
the neonatal unit says that

27:59.033 --> 28:01.266
keeping the baby alive is
actually cruel at this point.

28:01.333 --> 28:02.900
- I'm just trying
to catch up here, all right?

28:02.967 --> 28:04.633
I've had one meeting
with Alvarez.

28:04.700 --> 28:07.100
He sort of just
whined about his kid.

28:07.166 --> 28:09.133
- See, all I want is--
I just want him released

28:09.200 --> 28:10.467
so that I can take him
to the hospital,

28:10.533 --> 28:12.300
because I think that
when he sees the condition

28:12.367 --> 28:14.667
that the baby's in,
he will understand why

28:14.734 --> 28:16.333
they're going to take
the life support away.

28:16.400 --> 28:17.767
- I need more time.

28:17.834 --> 28:19.133
- We don't have time.

28:19.200 --> 28:20.734
They want to turn
the machines off tomorrow.

28:20.800 --> 28:22.900
- Tomor--
forget it.

28:22.967 --> 28:25.000
- Okay.

28:25.066 --> 28:27.200
I don't need his permission,
you know.

28:28.934 --> 28:30.200
- Well, yeah, but you're not--

28:30.266 --> 28:32.400
you're gonna take this
responsibility on yourself?

28:32.467 --> 28:33.867
- Absolutely.

28:35.800 --> 28:38.834
[buzzer sounds]

28:40.433 --> 28:43.367
[angelic choir singing]

28:43.433 --> 28:50.467
♪ ♪

29:01.166 --> 29:08.200
♪ ♪

29:26.934 --> 29:34.000
♪ ♪

29:46.066 --> 29:49.100
[flatline]

29:52.700 --> 29:55.567
- You know...
[clears throat]

29:55.633 --> 29:59.433
I appreciate everything
you've done for me...

30:00.900 --> 30:04.367
Especially, like, you know,
with the baby and all.

30:05.834 --> 30:08.033
Um--I mean, I--

30:08.100 --> 30:09.667
you know, I guess sometimes

30:09.734 --> 30:11.734
that's the way things go,
you know.

30:11.800 --> 30:15.233
I mean, things just
work out like that.

30:16.767 --> 30:18.667
You're right.

30:18.734 --> 30:21.834
You know, I feel--
I feel better about myself.

30:23.900 --> 30:26.500
I mean, I never thought that

30:26.567 --> 30:29.734
I'd--I'd love a baby
with all my heart.

30:32.066 --> 30:34.066
And I--you know,

30:34.133 --> 30:37.500
never loved anything before
in my life,

30:37.567 --> 30:39.000
so it's like it, like,
opened up,

30:39.066 --> 30:41.066
like, a whole--whole new me.

30:41.133 --> 30:43.233
[laughs softly]

30:44.133 --> 30:46.400
That's--that's important, right?

30:46.467 --> 30:48.100
Figuring out who you are,

30:48.166 --> 30:50.734
you know, and--and...

30:50.800 --> 30:53.700
about--about yourself.

30:54.934 --> 30:57.834
So, you know,
I know now.

30:59.467 --> 31:01.967
- Well, I'm real glad.

31:03.500 --> 31:06.333
- Well, you know,
I owe it all to you.

31:10.567 --> 31:13.166
- Well, I gotta go.

31:14.367 --> 31:16.300
- Hey father...

31:18.133 --> 31:21.200
where was God
when my son died?

31:22.266 --> 31:24.934
Same place he was
when his own son died.

31:36.200 --> 31:38.500
- It's looking pretty good.

31:38.567 --> 31:40.166
- I feel good.

31:40.233 --> 31:42.934
- Well, the remaining
kidney's functioning fine.

31:43.000 --> 31:44.500
The rest of you
is pretty healthy,

31:44.567 --> 31:46.934
so this afternoon I'll have you
transferred back to...

31:47.000 --> 31:48.166
- Death row.

31:48.233 --> 31:50.100
You can say it, Doctor.

31:50.166 --> 31:52.734
- Keane,
you have a visitor.

31:59.600 --> 32:00.633
- Hey, Pop.

32:00.700 --> 32:01.934
[both laugh softly]

32:09.433 --> 32:11.734
How's Grace?

32:13.300 --> 32:15.367
- Doctor says she recuperating

32:15.433 --> 32:17.400
faster than expected.

32:17.467 --> 32:19.633
That's some rocking kidney
you gave her.

32:19.700 --> 32:21.734
[laughs]

32:22.600 --> 32:24.133
- So how you doing?

32:24.200 --> 32:27.700
- I'm still a little turned
around by all this publicity.

32:27.767 --> 32:28.967
You know?

32:29.033 --> 32:31.367
Having a microphone
shoved in my face

32:31.433 --> 32:33.367
every time I leave the house.

32:33.433 --> 32:36.200
We've been getting lots of
letters and cards,

32:36.266 --> 32:37.767
mostly nice.
[chuckles]

32:37.834 --> 32:41.400
One guy from Iowa,
he sent $100 cash.

32:41.467 --> 32:44.533
Your Aunt Tilly said that
I had to send it back.

32:44.600 --> 32:45.700
- Did you?
- [laughs]

32:45.767 --> 32:47.133
- No fucking way.

32:47.200 --> 32:50.367
[both laugh]

32:53.200 --> 32:54.533
- Dad, um...

32:56.533 --> 32:57.934
I need for you
to do something for me.

32:58.000 --> 33:00.834
- Well, anything, son.
Come on now, you know that.

33:00.900 --> 33:04.433
- I need for you
to talk to Billie.

33:06.767 --> 33:08.533
- He's turned into a fag.

33:08.600 --> 33:10.367
- Dad, you don't know
what it's like in here.

33:10.433 --> 33:12.600
You don't know
the things they do to you.

33:12.667 --> 33:14.867
The loneliness.

33:14.934 --> 33:16.900
Talk to him.

33:16.967 --> 33:20.700
- I raised you three
all alone.

33:21.800 --> 33:24.233
Now your sister, she's--
[chuckles]

33:24.300 --> 33:26.934
she's gonna make something
with her life,

33:27.000 --> 33:29.600
especially with
what you done for her,

33:29.667 --> 33:31.433
but when he leaves...

33:31.500 --> 33:35.033
[scoffs]
What's Billie ever gonna be?

33:35.100 --> 33:39.166
- Your son,
my brother, forever.

33:41.533 --> 33:44.133
- Okay, time's up.

33:48.266 --> 33:50.000
- [quietly]
Hey, man...

33:53.734 --> 33:55.567
- It's rare when you
say good-bye to someone

33:55.633 --> 33:59.333
that you know
it's the last time.

33:59.400 --> 34:00.767
You could try to say
whatever it is

34:00.834 --> 34:02.600
you should have
said before.

34:02.667 --> 34:05.667
Or you can just
hold on tight.

34:07.200 --> 34:11.100
Just hold on hoping the moment
will last you a lifetime.

34:11.166 --> 34:16.166
♪ ♪

34:16.233 --> 34:17.934
- Shit!

34:18.000 --> 34:19.867
[strains, gasps]

34:19.934 --> 34:22.533
- You all right?

34:26.767 --> 34:28.767
- Jefferson...

34:28.834 --> 34:32.233
Was my oldest...

34:32.300 --> 34:35.033
So he always had
a special place.

34:37.767 --> 34:40.300
A man...

34:40.367 --> 34:44.000
shouldn't live
to see his own son die.

35:00.867 --> 35:04.567
- Hey, I-I brought you
some tea.

35:04.633 --> 35:06.166
- You brought me some tea?

35:06.233 --> 35:07.567
Why?

35:07.633 --> 35:10.033
- Well, it's herbal.

35:12.000 --> 35:13.867
Maybe you don't want it.

35:13.934 --> 35:16.500
- Hey,
just so happens I'm out.

35:16.567 --> 35:18.367
Thanks.

35:22.900 --> 35:25.533
So...
- So...

35:26.433 --> 35:29.000
- Why are you here, McManus?

35:29.066 --> 35:30.333
I mean, what do you want?

35:30.400 --> 35:32.500
- I don't know.

35:32.567 --> 35:34.967
I just, uh...

35:35.033 --> 35:38.266
I just wanted to tell you...

35:38.333 --> 35:41.166
that I'm sorry you're gonna die.

35:41.233 --> 35:42.467
And...

35:42.533 --> 35:44.767
- You'd like my forgiveness?

35:46.900 --> 35:50.100
Well, whatever
you think you've done...

35:50.166 --> 35:52.400
I forgive you.

35:59.333 --> 36:00.700
- Ooh.

36:00.767 --> 36:02.633
- Did you get
Kareem Said's test results?

36:02.700 --> 36:05.567
- Um...oh, that feels so good.

36:05.633 --> 36:07.200
So far, everything's fine.

36:07.266 --> 36:09.367
I'm just waiting
for the MRI results.

36:09.433 --> 36:11.367
Oh good.
You wanna go to dinner tonight?

36:11.433 --> 36:12.533
- I can't.

36:12.600 --> 36:14.567
- Why not?

36:14.633 --> 36:17.834
- I'm witnessing
Keane's execution.

36:22.433 --> 36:23.867
- What?

36:23.934 --> 36:25.066
- Yeah, I told you.

36:25.133 --> 36:27.133
- What?
You didn't tell me.

36:27.200 --> 36:29.333
Oh, man, you didn't tell me.
- Yes, I did.

36:29.400 --> 36:33.100
- Gloria, this is not something
I would forget, believe me.

36:33.166 --> 36:34.934
Christ!

36:35.000 --> 36:36.734
- Look, what is the big deal?
- [exhales]

36:36.800 --> 36:39.533
- I'm only prescribing
the drugs, declaring the death.

36:39.600 --> 36:41.734
It's not like I'm sticking
the I.V. in his arms.

36:41.800 --> 36:44.100
- Gloria...Gloria, doctors are
supposed to be healers.

36:44.166 --> 36:45.767
You're supposed
to help keep people alive.

36:45.834 --> 36:47.700
You're not supposed
to kill them.

36:47.767 --> 36:48.967
- You really see this
as a killing.

36:49.033 --> 36:51.133
- I don't want you doing this.

36:51.200 --> 36:53.066
- You what?
- I don't want you doing this!

36:53.133 --> 36:54.967
- Look, Tim,
we've only been going out

36:55.033 --> 36:56.467
for a couple of weeks, okay,
where do you get off

36:56.533 --> 36:57.834
telling me what I can
and can't do?

36:57.900 --> 37:00.467
- Don't--wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait.

37:00.533 --> 37:02.433
- Don't grab me.

37:05.600 --> 37:07.133
[sighs]

37:11.100 --> 37:14.066
You better take
some time off, Tim.

37:14.133 --> 37:15.333
You've been around
this prison so much

37:15.400 --> 37:18.633
you're starting
to act like them.

37:18.700 --> 37:21.734
[crowd yelling]

37:23.367 --> 37:25.033
- Hey, lady!

37:25.100 --> 37:28.133
[both shouting indistinctly]

37:34.867 --> 37:36.900
- Thanks.

37:41.734 --> 37:43.900
Is the governor here yet?

37:43.967 --> 37:46.567
- No, I haven't seen him.

37:46.633 --> 37:48.266
But a pro-death penalty marcher

37:48.333 --> 37:50.667
just took a swing
at Sister Pete.

37:50.734 --> 37:52.700
- Is she okay?

37:52.767 --> 37:54.033
- Good aim.

37:54.100 --> 37:57.033
She just kicked him
in the balls.

37:59.200 --> 38:02.500
I take it you're not
gonna watch the execution.

38:04.000 --> 38:05.400
- How about you?

38:05.467 --> 38:06.800
- Uh-uh.

38:06.867 --> 38:09.300
Can't stand
watching flowers die,

38:09.367 --> 38:12.467
let alone
another human being.

38:12.533 --> 38:14.533
Closest I ever came was Bambi.

38:14.600 --> 38:16.767
- "Bambi"?
- Yeah.

38:17.633 --> 38:20.633
My ex was a big hunter.

38:20.700 --> 38:22.133
He was always going off
with his buddies,

38:22.200 --> 38:25.166
so I said to him
one time "take me".

38:25.233 --> 38:27.734
After some complaining,
he did.

38:27.800 --> 38:29.400
So I got out there
in the forest

38:29.467 --> 38:31.200
with this, uh...
[chuckles]

38:31.266 --> 38:33.100
This big hunky shotgun

38:33.166 --> 38:36.200
and I fired at a deer.

38:36.266 --> 38:38.166
Hit it dead-on.

38:39.567 --> 38:41.433
So I went over to this thing

38:41.500 --> 38:44.000
and I leaned down and...

38:44.800 --> 38:48.333
This deer looked up at me
with these eyes,

38:48.400 --> 38:51.367
these eyes like flashlights.

38:52.667 --> 38:55.066
I knelt beside it
and I held its head

38:55.133 --> 38:57.900
and I whispered,
"I'm sorry".

39:00.133 --> 39:03.967
Then like batteries going bad,
the light in his eyes

39:04.033 --> 39:06.233
flickered a little bit

39:06.300 --> 39:08.333
and, uh...

39:08.400 --> 39:10.100
went out.

39:12.700 --> 39:14.233
For the next two years
that we were married,

39:14.300 --> 39:15.600
every time I walked
into the den,

39:15.667 --> 39:17.567
I had to stare at that
fucking deer's dead eyes.

39:17.633 --> 39:19.934
I had to dust them.

39:22.734 --> 39:24.633
When we got divorced,
that's all I asked for,

39:24.700 --> 39:27.300
the deer's head...

39:27.367 --> 39:29.533
and I buried it.

39:33.166 --> 39:36.033
- That's how I feel tonight.

39:36.100 --> 39:38.500
- What do you mean?

39:38.567 --> 39:41.834
- Like my head's hanging
on somebody's wall.

39:41.900 --> 39:44.834
[soft dramatic music]

39:44.900 --> 39:47.200
♪ ♪

39:47.266 --> 39:49.533
You wanna have dinner?

39:50.667 --> 39:51.600
- Sure.

39:51.667 --> 39:53.633
- Hey...

39:53.700 --> 39:54.934
- Yeah?

39:55.000 --> 39:56.133
- How you doing?

39:56.200 --> 39:59.000
- Okay.
You?

39:59.066 --> 40:01.967
- Not bad for a man
about to die.

40:02.033 --> 40:04.567
- Yeah, you go tonight, huh?

40:04.633 --> 40:07.066
- Yeah, you?

40:07.133 --> 40:09.233
- Next Thursday,

40:09.300 --> 40:10.967
but I'm in appeal.

40:11.033 --> 40:12.533
- You ever see that old movie?

40:12.600 --> 40:15.300
With--with that old actress--
what's her name?

40:15.367 --> 40:16.900
Susan Hayward?

40:16.967 --> 40:18.166
- Which movie?

40:18.233 --> 40:19.500
- I don't know.
It's called, um,

40:19.567 --> 40:21.133
"She's Gotta Live"
or something like that,

40:21.200 --> 40:25.066
she's on death row,
waiting to be fried or gassed

40:25.133 --> 40:26.867
or whatever they used to do
back in the day.

40:26.934 --> 40:30.633
Only thing, her attorney has
applied for some reprieve,

40:30.700 --> 40:34.433
so she just waits
and the clock keeps ticking,

40:34.500 --> 40:36.767
waiting for that call
from the governor.

40:36.834 --> 40:38.100
- Yeah...

40:38.166 --> 40:40.934
And at the last possible minute,
he calls, huh?

40:41.000 --> 40:42.800
- Well, you know,
now that I think about it,

40:42.867 --> 40:45.800
I think she fries.

40:50.533 --> 40:53.166
- I need to ask some questions.

40:58.300 --> 41:00.967
What do you want done
with your property?

41:01.033 --> 41:02.633
- Um...

41:02.700 --> 41:04.133
give it to my dad.

41:04.200 --> 41:06.600
- And the money
in your trust account?

41:06.667 --> 41:09.834
- To my brother and sister.

41:09.900 --> 41:12.667
- Will your family
be claiming your body?

41:15.100 --> 41:17.300
- Yeah.

41:18.033 --> 41:20.567
- Who are your witnesses?

41:20.633 --> 41:24.734
- My dad and
the Minister Said.

41:25.367 --> 41:27.233
- [sighs]

41:27.300 --> 41:30.533
You sure you should see this?

41:32.066 --> 41:33.700
- Yeah.

41:34.967 --> 41:37.834
Tizi and I have come
on a long journey together.

41:39.066 --> 41:41.767
I'm not going to turn
my back on him now.

41:43.734 --> 41:46.367
- [clears throat]
Okay...

41:46.433 --> 41:47.967
let's do it.

41:48.033 --> 41:49.700
Officer.

41:57.500 --> 42:00.300
- "Death is the supreme
moment of truth," my brother.

42:00.367 --> 42:03.033
So sayeth the Prophet.

42:03.100 --> 42:04.633
- Praise be unto him.

42:04.700 --> 42:07.367
- And peace be unto you.

42:07.433 --> 42:09.467
- Minister, they took my corfi.

42:09.533 --> 42:12.033
I don't wanna die out
without my corfi.

42:12.100 --> 42:14.233
- You take mine.

42:15.934 --> 42:19.433
[both speaking foreign language]

42:20.667 --> 42:24.800
- Over 3000 men and women are
sitting on death row right now.

42:24.867 --> 42:27.200
♪ ♪

42:27.266 --> 42:28.800
Congress has denied
state inmates

42:28.867 --> 42:31.100
access to federal courts.

42:31.166 --> 42:33.767
Congress has also
eliminated financing

42:33.834 --> 42:36.967
to law offices
for death row appeals.

42:37.033 --> 42:41.033
The states themselves are
shortening the appeals process.

42:41.100 --> 42:44.033
[dramatic music]

42:44.100 --> 42:51.166
♪ ♪

42:57.300 --> 42:59.100
- Lay down.

43:07.667 --> 43:10.133
- In this country,
there's now one execution

43:10.200 --> 43:13.133
every single week.

43:48.333 --> 43:50.367
There were more
executions this year

43:50.433 --> 43:54.400
than any time since the '50s.

43:55.266 --> 43:59.066
And we know how righteous
the 50s were.

44:03.100 --> 44:05.333
- You can make
any statement you'd like.

44:11.967 --> 44:14.734
- I want my family to know,

44:14.800 --> 44:16.700
that I love them.

44:16.767 --> 44:18.300
And I believe that
this punishes them

44:18.367 --> 44:21.000
more than it punishes me.

44:22.433 --> 44:24.066
I'm so sorry

44:24.133 --> 44:26.767
for the three murders
that I did.

44:26.834 --> 44:30.400
And I wish,
by killing me today,

44:30.467 --> 44:33.066
you could bring them back.

44:33.133 --> 44:34.834
My time on this Earth

44:34.900 --> 44:37.767
has been far too short.

44:37.834 --> 44:40.533
Maybe too short
to get it all done right.

44:41.900 --> 44:43.200
So...

44:45.300 --> 44:46.767
I'm ready
to move on.

44:46.834 --> 44:48.633
♪ ♪

44:48.700 --> 44:50.834
All praise...

44:50.900 --> 44:53.367
to Allah.

44:53.433 --> 44:55.567
All praise.

45:00.533 --> 45:02.633
- [gasps and shudders]

45:07.033 --> 45:10.300
- Governor?
- Justice has been served.

45:10.367 --> 45:13.400
- [grunting]

45:14.667 --> 45:16.667
- L'Italien...

45:16.734 --> 45:19.500
The Supreme Court refused
to hear your appeal.

45:19.567 --> 45:22.433
- Rehnquist is fag.

45:22.500 --> 45:23.767
- Be that as it may,

45:23.834 --> 45:26.633
your execution is
scheduled for tomorrow.

45:26.700 --> 45:30.800
Prisoner number 9-7-L-6-4-1
Richard L'Italien,

45:30.867 --> 45:34.467
convicted April 3rd, '97,
murder in the first degree.

45:34.533 --> 45:36.834
Sentence: death.

45:36.900 --> 45:38.600
- Tomorrow?

45:44.600 --> 45:46.767
Well, my schedule's clear.

45:46.834 --> 45:48.667
Okay.

45:48.734 --> 45:51.867
Hey, warden, there's something
I want to tell you.

45:51.934 --> 45:54.633
Something I never told anybody.

45:59.667 --> 46:02.000
I suffocated Jennifer Miller.

46:02.066 --> 46:03.934
- Yeah, I know.

46:04.000 --> 46:06.934
That's why you're gonna die.

46:07.000 --> 46:10.333
- I also suffocated
Dorothy Payne.

46:10.400 --> 46:11.567
- Who?

46:11.633 --> 46:13.467
- Dorothy Payne.

46:13.533 --> 46:16.200
She waitressed
up in Council Bluffs, Iowa.

46:18.300 --> 46:20.667
- You confessing another murder?

46:20.734 --> 46:23.500
- Uh-huh.

46:23.567 --> 46:26.767
- I'll notify
the proper authorities.

46:26.834 --> 46:28.333
- Wait.

46:28.400 --> 46:30.266
I also suffocated

46:30.333 --> 46:33.033
Ethel Peterson
and Gertrude Victor...

46:35.266 --> 46:37.734
And Mary Rapp

46:37.800 --> 46:39.767
and Christina Trudell

46:39.834 --> 46:41.767
and Eleanor Hughes,

46:41.834 --> 46:45.667
Wilma Lomax,
Lisa Masters,

46:45.734 --> 46:47.600
And Lorraine McCarthy,

46:47.667 --> 46:49.867
and Betty Case,

46:49.934 --> 46:51.300
and Irene Martin,

46:51.367 --> 46:55.033
and Amelia Nugent,
Elizabeth Phelps,

46:55.100 --> 46:57.166
and Lucille Upton,

46:57.233 --> 46:59.300
and Esther Voght.

46:59.367 --> 47:01.600
[chuckles]
What I did.

47:01.667 --> 47:05.400
- Richard L'Italien confessed
to 39 murders,

47:05.467 --> 47:08.467
all young women.
He suffocated them all.

47:08.533 --> 47:09.834
- If the governor
had his way,

47:09.900 --> 47:13.133
he would execute L'Italien
39 times.

47:14.033 --> 47:15.767
- I have to get over there.

47:15.834 --> 47:19.934
- Ray, listen...

47:20.000 --> 47:22.200
how can you
go along with this?

47:22.266 --> 47:24.633
You're as much against
the death penalty as I am.

47:24.700 --> 47:26.200
- Of course I am, Pete.

47:26.266 --> 47:27.633
I don't know.

47:27.700 --> 47:29.834
Maybe if anyone
deserves to die,

47:29.900 --> 47:31.467
Richard L'Italien
deserves to die.

47:31.533 --> 47:32.800
Maybe the world will,
what?

47:32.867 --> 47:34.834
Breathe a little easier
once he's gone.

47:34.900 --> 47:37.200
My job is not
to make judgments.

47:37.266 --> 47:40.700
My job is to be
by his side.

47:40.767 --> 47:42.734
My place...

47:42.800 --> 47:46.033
is with him.

47:46.100 --> 47:48.500
If he needs me.

47:52.066 --> 47:54.133
[whispers]
Pray for him, Mary.

47:57.100 --> 47:58.667
That's for him.

48:00.834 --> 48:02.800
That's for all of them.

48:12.433 --> 48:15.567
- Have you ever had
bull's balls, Father?

48:15.633 --> 48:17.767
- No, sir, I can't
say that I have.

48:17.834 --> 48:19.333
- Well, they serve them
every year

48:19.400 --> 48:22.533
at the Bohemian Grove.

48:22.600 --> 48:23.934
- What's that,
